# Free Intelligence - Git Attributes
# Ensures consistent line endings across platforms

# Auto-detect text files and normalize line endings
* text=auto

# Source code - always LF
*.py text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.txt text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf

# Committed build artifacts — tracked on purpose, but NEVER worth reviewing.
#
# The two published packages ship their built dist/ deliberately: og118 resolves
# fi-glass's exports straight to dist/ and its CI never rebuilds the package, so
# source and bundle must land together (.claude/rules/committed-dist-artifacts.md).
#
# The cost is that a tracked bundle floods every review. On the shell-consolidation
# PR the dist/ diff was 5,516 lines against 723 lines of real source change — 88%
# noise — and the AI Gatekeeper, whose payload IS that diff, reported three times
# that `src/shell/index.ts` "is not in the diff" while it demonstrably was. It was
# not hallucinating: the source changes had been pushed out of its context by
# generated bytes no reviewer can usefully read.
#
# `linguist-generated` collapses these in GitHub's review UI; `-diff` makes git
# omit their content from the textual diff. The files stay TRACKED and still ship.
# Only their diff stops drowning the change that needs judgement.
apps/packages/fi-glass/dist/** linguist-generated=true -diff
apps/packages/free-intelligence-core/dist/** linguist-generated=true -diff
*.map linguist-generated=true -diff

# Binary files - never modify
*.h5 binary
*.bundle binary
*.sha256 binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
